• El also recalls that her son may have gone to Palm Beach with once because he

• E estimates that was traveling to Palm Beach for work for approximately two 
and a half years when she was a teenager. 
• El did not see the contents of the packages received, but she remembers 
having books about massage and promiscuous clothing after receiving those

• • recalls the following callers to her phone regarding work in Palm Beach: 
o Two male voices: 
• One was a car service or driver picking 
up 
• The second E remembers calling to say he was sending a car to pick 
up 
o Two female voices: 
• One named called multiple times. 
• One with an accent called multiple times. 
• 
believes this woman's 
name was something like Giselle Maxine 
• • recalls the female caller with an accent being particularly unpleasant in her tone 
during one call, during which the female caller said that and her friends were 
supposed to be at the house for a party. • assumed that meant and her friends 
were supposed to set up for some party. 
• El did not realize that had been sexually abused by Jeffrey Epstein until the FBI 
knocked 
on 
door in or about 2007 as part of an investigation. never 
explicitly told E what happened to her with Epstein, and no one from law enforcement 
ever explicitly told E what happened either, but E gathered over the years from 
behavior, law enforcement interactions, and civil suits that Epstein must have 
abused her. 
• After E went to GA, at some point told U that E and E were 
getting cocaine from the house they were cleaning in Palm Beach. U didn't say who 
actually ave them cocaine. • told U that U was cleaning houses. 
• Since IE has gotten out of jail in 2020, E has spoken with him a handful of times about 
his son. • told E that he was subpoenaed, but he otherwise did not tell her anything 
else. • told E recently that E asked her for money.
